{
  "texts": [
    "\"The Text,\" he tells us, \"is that which goes to the limit of the rules of enunciation (rationality, readability, etc.).\"",
    "Text is a process that cannot be \"computed\"; it is always \"subversive […] in respect of the old classifications\".",
    "Given the enactment of fixed ontologies and value systems, ChatGPT cannot achieve this staking forward of boundaries, because by design it is bound to established patterns.",
    "Thus, ChatGPT does not make transgressive Texts.",
    "The subject is a self-conducting subject partly insofar as it resists, but in being limited to the \"computable\", ChatGPT conforms, and in always conforming, it never resists."
  ]
}